modules.description: Provides functions for loading and accessing data in a page-by-page manner, using a map function to interface with block devices. Operates on memory-mapped buffers and page indices to enable efficient, atomic read operations. Used to optimize sequential access to large files or disk regions by minimizing repeated I/O operations.

Establishes a connection to a Cachet server with a specified cache size, returning a file descriptor wrapped in a Cachet container. Operates on string endpoints and file descriptor types to manage network communication. Used to interface with distributed caching systems in low-level network applications.
